  "response": "Okay, let's find the best MacBook for you! To give you the best recommendation, I need a little more information about how you plan to use it.  Please tell me about:\n\n**1. Budget:**  Roughly how much are you willing to spend? (e.g., Under $1000, $1000-$1500, $1500-$2000, $2000+)\n\n**2. Primary Use Cases:** What will you be using the MacBook for *most* of the time?  Be as specific as possible.  Here are some examples:\n\n*   **General Use:**  Web browsing, email, document creation (Word, Google Docs), social media, streaming videos (Netflix, YouTube).\n*   **Student:**  Note-taking, research, writing papers, running student software (e.g., engineering programs), presentations.\n*   **Work (Office):**  Email, spreadsheets (Excel), presentations (PowerPoint), video conferencing (Zoom, Teams), project management software.\n*   **Creative Work (Photo Editing):**  Adobe Photoshop, Lightroom, Capture One.  How large are the files you typically work with?\n*   **Creative Work (Video Editing):**  Final Cut Pro, Adobe Premiere Pro.  What resolution will you be editing (1080p, 4K, 6K, 8K)?\n*   **Creative Work (Graphic Design):**  Adobe Illustrator, InDesign.\n*   **Creative Work (Music Production):**  Logic Pro, Ableton Live.\n*   **Software Development:**  Coding, running virtual machines, compiling code.  What languages/frameworks do you use?\n*   **Gaming:**  (MacBooks aren't generally known for gaming, but some can handle certain games.  Be specific about the types of games you want to play.)\n\n**3. Portability:** How important is it that the MacBook be lightweight and easy to carry around?\n\n*   **Very Important:**  Need something super light and compact for frequent travel or carrying around campus.\n*   **Somewhat Important:**  Will be moving it occasionally, but not constantly.\n*   **Not Important:**  Will mostly stay on a desk.\n\n**4. Screen Size Preference:** Do you have a preference for screen size?\n\n*   **Smaller (13-14 inch):** More portable.\n*   **Larger (16 inch):** More screen real estate for multitasking.\n\n**5. Storage Needs:** How much storage do you think you'll need?\n\n*   **256GB:**  Okay for basic use, documents, and some photos.  Might need to rely on cloud storage.\n*   **512GB:**  Good for a decent amount of files, photos, and some video projects.\n*   **1TB or More:**  Recommended for large video projects, extensive photo libraries, or lots of software.\n\n**6. How long do you plan to keep the MacBook?**\n\n*   **A few years (3-4):** A base model might be sufficient\n*   **Long term (5+ years):** Investing in more RAM and storage could be worth it.\n\n**7. Any other specific requirements or preferences?**\n\n*   Do you need a specific number of ports (e.g., USB-C, HDMI)?\n*   Do you have any preferences for color?\n*   Do you need a particularly good webcam for video conferencing?\n*   Are you a student or educator who can take advantage of education pricing?\n\nOnce I have this information, I can give you a much more tailored and helpful recommendation!\n",
